paragraphs:
Types of received data:

- physical samples;
- data of computational experiments (recorded in xlsx and jpg format)
- data of synthetic procedures of samples (recorded in xlsx or doc format);
- laboratory experiments data dedicated to synthetic procedures – e.g., spectral analysis of samples (recored in xlsx, csv, fid formats);
- laboratory experiments data dedicated to biological assays (recored in xlsx format);
- laboratory notes stored in the laboratory notebooks (hardcopy).

The predicted total volume of achieved and analyzed data will be in the range 10-100 GB.

